<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="695" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3281</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-26T20:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.43 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1383. Minister for Foreign Affairs informed me to-day that
                                representatives of Norway Foreign Office, Department of Justice,
                                Secret Service and Legation at Petrograd have gone to Copenhagen to
                                meet Swedish and Danish representatives with a view to working out a
                                uniform policy in regard to Bolshevism.</p>
                            <p>In reply to a question Minister of Foreign Affairs stated that this
                                Government does not anticipate an actual Bolshevik outbreak in
                                Norway.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>